/KAAn Arab Shepherd Is Searching for His Goat on Mount Zion/XX/PR

An Arab shepherd is searching for his goat/PR

on Mount Zion,/PR

And on the opposite hill I am searching for my little boy./PR

An Arab shepherd and a Jewish father/PR

Both in their temporary failure./PR

Our two voices meet above/PR

The Sultanòs Pool in the valley between us./PR

Neither of us wants the boy or the goat/PR

To get caught in the wheels/PR

of the "H/±ad Gadya" machine./PR

/PR

Afterward we found them among the bushes,/PR

And our voices came back inside us/PR

Laughing and crying./PR

/PR

Searching for a goat or for a child has always been/PR

The beginning of a new religion in these mountains./PR

Yehuda Amichai/XX/PR

