/PL819/XXREADINGS: MEMORIAL DAY/XX/PR

/KAMEMORIAL DAY/PR

The Young Dead Soldiers/XX/PR

The young dead soldiers do not speak./PR

Nevertheless they are heard in the still houses./PR

(Who has not heard them?)/PR

They have a silence that speaks for them at night/PR

And when the clock counts./PR

They say,/PR

We were young. We have died. Remember us./PR

They say,/PR

We have done what we could/PR

But until it is finished it is not done./PR

They say,/PR

We have given our lives/PR

But until it is finished no one can know what our lives gave./PR

They say,/PR

Our deaths are not ours,/PR

They are yours,/PR

They will mean what you make them./PR

They say,/PR

Whether our lives and our deaths were for peace and a new hope/PR

Or for nothing/PR

We cannot say./PR

It is you who must say this./PR

They say,/PR

We leave you our deaths./PR

Give them their meaning./PR

Give them an end to the war and a true peace,/PR

Give them a victory that ends the war and a peace afterwards,/PR

Give them their meaning./PR

We were young, they say./PR

We have died./PR

Remember us./PR

Archibald MacLeish/XX/PR

