/KAFish Crier/XX/PR

I know a Jew[ish] fish crier down on Maxwell Street with a/PR


voice like a north wind blowing over corn stubble in January./PR

He dangles herring before prospective customers evincing a joy/PR


identical with that of Pavlowa dancing./PR

His face is that of a man terribly glad to be selling fish, terribly/PR


glad that God made fish, and customers to whom he may/PR


call his wares from a pushcart./PR

Carl Sandburg/XX/PR

