/KATHANKSGIVING/PR

She Was Like No Doll Iòd Ever Seen.../XX/PR

When I sat down at the table for breakfast, the doll was at my
place. Mama had made hair out of dark brown yarn and sheòd
embroidered eyes, a nose, and a mouth on the face. She had
covered the yarn hair with a yellow kerchief embroidered with
red flowers./PR

"Sheòs gorgeous, Mama," I managed to murmur. "But she
doesnòt look like the Pilgrim woman in the picture."/PR

"No?" Mama said./PR

"She looks like you in that photograph you have that was taken
when you were a girl."/PR

"Of course," Mama said. "I did that on purpose. Whatòs a
Pilgrim, /ITshaynkeit/XX? A Pilgrim is someone who came here from
the other side to find freedom. Thatòs me, Molly. Iòm a
Pilgrim!"/PR

Barbara Cohen/XX/PR

/PR

/PR

